author: @alexcoventry7580
text: Spoiler alert: This series of talks only glancingly touches on sentiment analysis.  In the end it covers some very crude statistical clean up (truncating price moves over 20 standard deviations seems a bit silly... wouldn't the best opportunities be right there??) and a crude moving-average crossover trading strategy which badly underperforms the market, even when backtested without accounting for trading costs or slippage.  If this was meant as an ad for sentdex, it's a bit strange.  Why provide that fancy data set and then never use it?  Maybe halfway through the author found a trading strategy so profitable that he decided to keep it under his hat? :-)
